  "texts": [
    "To validate the safety, accuracy, and professionalism of the question-answering system, this study employed the SUS (15) (Safety, Usability, Smoothness) evaluation method.",
    "A comparative evaluation will be conducted between a question-answering system integrated with LLM and knowledge graphs, and a LLM without RAG technology.",
    "The SUS evaluation method consists of three dimensions: safety, usability, and smoothness.",
    "Safety evaluates whether the model-generated content could mislead users and pose potential health risks; usability assesses whether the content meets professional knowledge requirements; smoothness examines the response stability and naturalness of the model.",
    "SUS employs a three-point scoring system, with scores ranging from 1 (unacceptable) to 3 (good), where 2 indicates acceptable performance."
  ],
